{"title":"Wand of draining","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Wand_of_draining","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n| Type | Wand                                                                                     |\n| :--- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name | wand of draining                                                                         |\n| Icon | [![Wand of draining.png](/images/8/88/Wand_of_draining.png)](/File:Wand_of_draining.png) |\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                                                                                     |\n| - | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | A magical device which throws a bolt of negative energy which drains the life essences of living creatures, but is useless against the undead, demons, artificial creatures and even living plants. |\n\nA **wand of draining** is a \"tier-1\" attack wand which projects bolts of [negative energy](/Negative_energy \"Negative energy\"), similar to the spell [Bolt of Draining](/Bolt_of_Draining \"Bolt of Draining\"). These deal damage and reduce the target's [HD](/HD \"HD\"), rendering them weaker (and also less valuable in terms of XP).\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Player Use](#Player_Use)\n- [2 Monster Use](#Monster_Use)\n- [3 Tips & Tricks](#Tips_.26_Tricks)\n- [4 History](#History)\n\n## Player Use\n\nAs usual for wands, the beam from a wand of draining zapped by the player has a power rating of (30 + 2d([Evocations](/Evocations \"Evocations\") skill)).\n\n## Monster Use\n\nAs with any other wand, the bolt of draining projected by a wand of draining in the hands of a monster uses a power rating of (30 + (monster hit dice)). This gives it a typical damage output of 3d8 when used by low-level monsters and 3d9 when used by mid-to-high level monsters, and the player needs EV 19 to have a 50% chance of evading the beam without Repel or Deflect Missiles in force.\n\n## Tips & Tricks\n\nAs a tier-1 attack wand, wands of draining provide a powerful backup attack. Melee characters should save them for living opponents that are unusually dangerous to engage in melee, such as [hydras](/Hydra \"Hydra\") and acidic monsters. [Ice Magic](/Ice_Magic \"Ice Magic\") and [Fire Magic](/Fire_Magic \"Fire Magic\") users should use them as a backup or alternate attack against living opponents that resist their elemental attack spells; very few living monsters have any [Life Protection](/Life_Protection \"Life Protection\") at all.\n\n## History\n\nWands of draining was removed in [0.18](/0.18 \"0.18\").\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Wand of draining - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Wand_of_draining\",\"wgTitle\":\"Wand of draining\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":41703,\"wgRevisionId\":41703,\"wgArticleId\":559,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Obsolete articles\",\"Wand\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",